  "commentary": "With SPX at 6580.18 sitting just below the 6593 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are currently long gamma and will sell any rally toward the massive 6600 wall (26.8B GEX) while providing support on dips toward 6550. The 154.7% 1-min GEX surge and wall break event suggest dealers are aggressively hedging into this level, creating a strong magnet effect around current prices with the 6580 strike itself holding significant positive gamma (15B). Key levels: 6550 downside support where dealers turn buyers, 6593 flip point, and 6600 resistance wall where dealer selling intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6550-6600 with a gravitational pull toward 6580.",
